 Funktionen dieser Aspekte in der Darstellung des Tanzes in den unterschiedlichen medialen Ausdrucksformen nach.  aHow do writers, artists and filmmakers interpret Spanish dance culture? Which forms and functions reappear time and again, which motifs are negotiated across different media?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aPainting. 4aAvantgarde. 4aDrama. 4aFilm. 4aGender Studies. 4aInterkulturalität. 4aIntermedialität. 4aKunstgeschichte des 20. Jahrhunderts. 4aLiteratur. 4aLyrik. 4aMalerei. 4aPerformativität. 4aRhythmus. 4aRoman. 4aSpanische Literatur. 4aStummfilm. 4aTanz. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Dance / General.2bisacsh  aArt History of the 20th Century.  aAvant-garde.  aDance.  aDrama.  aFilm.  aGender Studies.  aInterculturalism.  aIntermediality.  aLiterature.  aNovel.  aPainting.  aPerformativity.  aPoetry.  aRhythm.  aSilent Film.  aSpanish Literature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2016z9783110485264oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070101208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839431078zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839431078423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839431078/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070101-2  PP Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_P